# This is how you automated tasks with Cron in Linux
# Automated Tasks:
# gedit /etc/crontab:
# Example shutdown at 9:00PM everyday:
# 00 21 * * * root shutdown -h now
# Cron Format:
# MM HH DD OO WW command
# MM: Minute, 0-59
# HH: 24-hour hour
# DD: Day of month
# OO: Month
# WW: Day of Week (Sunday is 0, Monday is 1)
# command: Self-explanatory
